344. Reverse String Description Write a function that reverses a string. The input string is given as an array of characters s.
&nbsp;
Example 1:
Input: s = ["h","e","l","l","o"]Output: ["o","l","l","e","h"]Example 2:
Input: s = ["H","a","n","n","a","h"]Output: ["h","a","n","n","a","H"]&nbsp;
Constraints:
1 &lt;= s.length &lt;= 105s[i] is a printable ascii character.&nbsp;
Follow up: Do not allocate extra space for another array.
